  <h2 id="system-setup">System Setup: Kidney Loop Configuration</h2>

  <p>
    Lube oil centrifuges are installed in a <strong>kidney loop</strong> arrangement, continuously processing oil from the reservoir and returning clean oil. The typical setup includes:
  </p>

  <ol>
    <li>A feed pump draws oil from the <strong>bottom of the reservoir</strong> (where contaminants settle)</li>
    <li>The oil passes through an <strong>inline pre-heater</strong> to reduce viscosity and improve separation efficiency</li>
    <li>The heated oil enters the centrifuge, where water, particles, and sludge are separated</li>
    <li>Clean oil returns to the <strong>top of the reservoir</strong></li>
    <li>Separated water drains to a collection point; sludge is ejected or removed during cleaning</li>
  </ol>

  <p>
    This arrangement continuously polishes the oil without interrupting turbine or engine operation. The centrifuge processes the entire reservoir volume multiple times per day, maintaining ISO cleanliness targets.
  </p>

